From: Shannon Nelson <shannon.nelson@amd.com>
Date: Mon, 11 Dec 2023 10:57:57 -0800
Subject: ionic: pass opcode to devcmd_wait
Patch-mainline: v6.8-rc1
Git-commit: 24f110240c03c6b5368f1203bac72883d511e606
References: jsc#PED-6953

Don't rely on the PCI memory for the devcmd opcode because we
read a 0xff value if the PCI bus is broken, which can cause us
to report a bogus dev_cmd opcode later.

Signed-off-by: Shannon Nelson <shannon.nelson@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Brett Creeley <brett.creeley@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_dev.c  |    1 +
 drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_dev.h  |    1 +
 drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_main.c |    2 +-
 3 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_dev.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_dev.c
@@ -321,6 +321,7 @@ void ionic_dev_cmd_comp(struct ionic_dev
 
 void ionic_dev_cmd_go(struct ionic_dev *idev, union ionic_dev_cmd *cmd)
 {
+	idev->opcode = cmd->cmd.opcode;
 	memcpy_toio(&idev->dev_cmd_regs->cmd, cmd, sizeof(*cmd));
 	iowrite32(0, &idev->dev_cmd_regs->done);
 	iowrite32(1, &idev->dev_cmd_regs->doorbell);
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_dev.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_dev.h
@@ -153,6 +153,7 @@ struct ionic_dev {
 	bool fw_hb_ready;
 	bool fw_status_ready;
 	u8 fw_generation;
+	u8 opcode;
 
 	u64 __iomem *db_pages;
 	dma_addr_t phy_db_pages;
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/pensando/ionic/ionic_main.c
@@ -443,7 +443,7 @@ static int __ionic_dev_cmd_wait(struct i
 	 */
 	max_wait = jiffies + (max_seconds * HZ);
 try_again:
-	opcode = readb(&idev->dev_cmd_regs->cmd.cmd.opcode);
+	opcode = idev->opcode;
 	start_time = jiffies;
 	for (fw_up = ionic_is_fw_running(idev);
 	     !done && fw_up && time_before(jiffies, max_wait);
